lines.meaning:
They bear and endure;
This means good fortune for inferior people.
The standstill serves to help the great one to attain success.

One hides weapons in the thicket;
One climbs the high hill in front of it.
For three years one does not rise up.

An open one loses their carriage's curtain.
Do not run after it;
On the seventh day you will get it.
